{
  "enabled": true,
  "name": "FDE Pipeline Validation",
  "description": "Phase 3.b-3.d and Phase 4 of the FDE protocol. After task completion, enforces pipeline-level testing, 5W2H reasoning, 5 Whys for issues found, and structured completion report. Enable this hook when using the #fde steering.",
  "version": "2.0.0",
  "when": {
    "type": "postTaskExecution"
  },
  "then": {
    "type": "askAgent",
    "prompt": "FDE PROTOCOL — PHASE 3.b-3.d + PHASE 4\n\nAs a Forward Deployed AI Engineer, execute these validation steps before reporting to the user.\n\n## 3.b Pipeline Testing\n- CONTRACT: Run contract tests — do the cross-layer invariants pass?\n- EDGE: Does the output of the changed module match what the next module expects?\n- PRODUCT: Run product smoke test if it exists. If not, state: 'No product-level smoke test — pipeline output not validated end-to-end.'\n\n## 3.c 5W2H Validation\nAnswer for the delivered task:\n- WHAT was changed and what does it produce?\n- WHERE in the pipeline does this sit?\n- WHEN does it take effect (build time, runtime, publish time)?\n- WHO is affected?\n- WHY this approach vs alternatives?\n- HOW was it validated? Which test scopes were run?\n- HOW MUCH of the pipeline was tested (node only, edge, end-to-end)?\n\n## 3.d 5 Whys (if issues were found during this task)\nFor each issue:\n1. State the symptom\n2. Apply 5 Whys to the root cause\n3. Confirm the fix addresses the root cause, not the symptom\n4. Confirm the fix prevents the bug CLASS, not just this instance\n\n## Phase 4: Completion Report\nSummarize for the user:\n- What was delivered\n- What was validated (and how — which test scopes, which edges)\n- What was NOT validated (and why)\n- Any residual risks or follow-up items"
  }
}
